  <abstract>This document explains the Title XX of the Social Security Act, which became effective on Oct. 1, 1975. Title XX provided money to each state for a broad range of social service programs, such as child daycare, homemaker services, senior citizens programs, services to the handicapped, protective services, and legal services.</abstract>
